{"title_page": "Mighty Little Bheem", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Mighty Little Bheem\n| image                    = Mighty Little Bheem poster.jpg\n| genre                    = Comedy\n| creator                  = Rajiv Chilaka\n| based_on                 = [[Chhota Bheem]]\n| director                 =\n| voices                   =\n| composer                 =\n| country                  =\n| language                 =\n| num_seasons              = 2\n| num_episodes             = 49\n| list_episodes            =\n| executive_producer       =\n| producer                 =\n| runtime                  = 6 minutes\n| company                  = [[Green Gold Animations]]\n| distributor              =\n| network                  = [[Netflix]]\n| picture_format           =\n| audio_format             =\n| first_aired              =\n| last_aired               =\n| related                  = [[Chhota Bheem]]<br>[[Mighty Raju]]<br>[[Arjun - Prince of Bali]]<br>[[Super Bheem]]\n| website                  = https://www.netflix.com/title/80212481\n| production_website       =\n}}\n\n'''''Mighty Little Bheem''''' is a [[computer animation|computer animated]] [[children's television series]], Netflix's first animated series from India and the fourth spin-off of Chhota Bheem series, following [[Mighty Raju]], [[Arjun - Prince of Bali]] and Super Bheem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/television/report-inpired-from-chota-bheem-netflix-to-launch-first-animated-series-mighty-little-bheem-2553228|title=Inpired from Chhota Bheem, Netflix to launch first animated series 'Mighty Little Bheem'|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref> It follows an innocent but super-strong toddler, Little Bheem, on his mischievous adventures in a small Indian town. The toddler is a baby version of the mythological-inspired 9-year-old character from the popular Indian series action comedy animated series [[Chhota Bheem]] which has aired on Turner Broadcasting\u2019s Pogo TV channel from 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/asia/netflix-enters-indian-kids-space-with-mighty-little-bheem-1202590762/|title=Netflix Enters Indian Kids\u2019 Space With \u2018Mighty Little Bheem\u2019|date=16 October 2017|first=Naman|last=Ramachandran|work=Variety|accessdate=21 September 2019}}</ref>  Chhota Bheem is in turn based on Bheem, a  character in the Sanskrit epic Mahabharata.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://decider.com/2019/04/15/mighty-little-bheem-netflix-stream-it-or-skip-it/|title=Stream It Or Skip It: \u2018Mighty Little Bheem\u2019 On Netflix, An Indian Animated Series About A Really Strong Toddler|website=Decider|accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nIn 2016, after the launch of Netflix in India, Aram Yacoubian, director of kids and family content at the US streaming service, first met Rajiv Chilaka of Green Gold Animation, and agreed on a series that would target the age group of 6-11. To make it universal, the decision was made to make it non-verbal. The show was in production for 18 months, starting in July 2017 and led by Green Gold\u2019s teams in Hyderabad and Mumbai.<ref name=\"economictimes\">{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/mighty-little-bheem-netflixs-first-indian-animation-show-for-children-becomes-a-global-hit/articleshow/69642719.cms|newspaper=The Economic Times|title='Mighty Little Bheem': Netflix\u2019s first Indian animation show for children becomes a global hit|accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Green Gold Animations]] has become one of India\u2019s largest toon companies, with studios in Hyderabad, Mumbai and Kolkata, as well as international outposts in Los Angeles, Singapore and the Philippines.<ref name=\"economictimes\" />\n\n==Release==\n''Mighty Little Bheem'' season 1 was released on 12 April 2019 on Netflix streaming.<ref>{{cite movie|url=https://www.netflix.com/title/80211492|title=Mighty Little Bheem|publisher=Netflix}}</ref> Season 2 was released on August 30 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/business/story/2019-08-25/netflix-invests-more-in-global-animated-series-like-indias-mighty-little-bheem|title=Netflix's renewal of this Indian animated show reveals how its chasing growth abroad|date=26 August 2019|website=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\n\n==Special==\nA special episode titled ''Mighty Little Bheem: Diwali'' on October 27, 2019 on the occasion of [[Diwali]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/oct/01/mighty-little-bheem-to-get-third-season-on-netflix-2041864.html|title='Mighty Little Bheem' to get third season on Netflix|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Netflix title|80211492}}\n* {{IMDb title|10050752}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|mighty_little_bheem}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Animation|India|Television}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Indian television series]]\n[[Category:2019 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Chhota Bheem]]\n[[Category:Indian animated television series]]\n[[Category:Indian children's television series]]\n[[Category:Indian programmes distributed by Netflix]]\n[[Category:Indian television spin-offs]]\n[[Category:Indian computer-animation]]\n[[Category:Television series by Netflix Animation]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Mighty Little Bheem\n| image                    = Mighty Little Bheem poster.jpg\n| genre                    = Comedy\n| creator                  = Rajiv Chilaka\n| based_on                 = [[Chhota Bheem]]\n| director                 =\n| voices                   =\n| composer                 =\n| country                  =\n| language                 =\n| num_seasons              = 2\n| num_episodes             = 49\n| list_episodes            =\n| executive_producer       =\n| producer                 =\n| runtime                  = 6 minutes\n| company                  = [[Green Gold Animations]]\n| distributor              =\n| network                  = [[Netflix]]\n| picture_format           =\n| audio_format             =\n| first_aired              =\n| last_aired               =\n| related                  = [[Chhota Bheem]]<br>[[Mighty Raju]]<br>[[Arjun - Prince of Bali]]<br>[[Super Bheem]]\n| website                  = https://www.netflix.com/title/80212481\n| production_website       =\n}}\n\n'''''Mighty Little Bheem''''' is a [[computer animation|computer animated]] [[children's television series]], Netflix's first animated series from India and the fourth spin-off of Chhota Bheem series, following [[Mighty Raju]], [[Arjun - Prince of Bali]] and Super Bheem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/television/report-inpired-from-chota-bheem-netflix-to-launch-first-animated-series-mighty-little-bheem-2553228|title=Inpired from Chhota Bheem, Netflix to launch first animated series 'Mighty Little Bheem'|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref> It follows an innocent but super-strong toddler, Little Bheem, on his mischievous adventures in a small Indian town. The toddler is a baby version of the mythological-inspired 9-year-old character from the popular Indian series action comedy animated series [[Chhota Bheem]] which has aired on Turner Broadcasting\u2019s Pogo TV channel from 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/asia/netflix-enters-indian-kids-space-with-mighty-little-bheem-1202590762/|title=Netflix Enters Indian Kids\u2019 Space With \u2018Mighty Little Bheem\u2019|date=16 October 2017|first=Naman|last=Ramachandran|work=Variety|accessdate=21 September 2019}}</ref>  Chhota Bheem is in turn based on Bheem, a  character in the Sanskrit epic Mahabharata.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://decider.com/2019/04/15/mighty-little-bheem-netflix-stream-it-or-skip-it/|title=Stream It Or Skip It: \u2018Mighty Little Bheem\u2019 On Netflix, An Indian Animated Series About A Really Strong Toddler|website=Decider|accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nIn 2016, after the launch of Netflix in India, Aram Yacoubian, director of kids and family content at the US streaming service, first met Rajiv Chilaka of Green Gold Animation, and agreed on a series that would target the age group of 6-11. To make it universal, the decision was made to make it non-verbal. The show was in production for 18 months, starting in July 2017 and led by Green Gold\u2019s teams in Hyderabad and Mumbai.<ref name=\"economictimes\">{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/mighty-little-bheem-netflixs-first-indian-animation-show-for-children-becomes-a-global-hit/articleshow/69642719.cms|newspaper=The Economic Times|title='Mighty Little Bheem': Netflix\u2019s first Indian animation show for children becomes a global hit|accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Green Gold Animations]] has become one of India\u2019s largest toon companies, with studios in Hyderabad, Mumbai and Kolkata, as well as international outposts in Los Angeles, Singapore and the Philippines.<ref name=\"economictimes\" />\n\n==Release==\n''Mighty Little Bheem'' season 1 was released on 12 April 2019 on Netflix streaming.<ref>{{cite movie|url=https://www.netflix.com/title/80211492|title=Mighty Little Bheem|publisher=Netflix}}</ref> season 2 was released on August 30 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/business/story/2019-08-25/netflix-invests-more-in-global-animated-series-like-indias-mighty-little-bheem|title=Netflix's renewal of this Indian animated show reveals how its chasing growth abroad|date=26 August 2019|website=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\n\n==Special==\nA special episode titled ''Mighty Little Bheem: Diwali'' on October 27, 2019 on the occasion of [[Diwali]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/oct/01/mig