{London Underground Rolling Stock}}\n\n[[Category:London Underground electric multiple units|A]]\n[[Category:Train-related introductions in 1934]]\n\n\n{{London-tube-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2017}}\n{{Infobox train\n|name         = Circle Stock\n|image        = \n|caption      = \n|manufacturer = Acton Works\n|service      = 1934-1950\n|family       = \n|replaced     = \n|lines        = \n|carlength    = \n|trainlength  = \n|width        = \n|height       = \n|maxspeed     = \n|weight       = \n|seating      = \n|stocktype    = [[London Underground infrastructure#Subsurface versus deep-level tube lines|Subsurface]]\n|notes        = {{Portal-inline|size=tiny|London transport}}\n}}\n[[File:Circle stock.JPG|thumb|Model of Circle Stock]]\nThe '''London Underground Circle Stock''' consist 9 cars renovated in 1934 at Acton Works, selected by the LPTB from earlier [[Metropolitan Railway]] stock - mainly dating from the early 1920s but some from 1906. Th e vehicles were externally repainted in a red-and-cream livery at first; later all-red. They operated in five-car formations.\n\nThey were finally withdrawn on 31 December 1950, being replaced by 5-car trains of [[London Underground O Stock|P Stock]], which had previously been used on the [[Uxbridge Underground station|Uxbridge]] branch of the Metropolitan Line.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Circle Stock Fleet Details<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=May 1986|title=Underground News May 1986|url=http://www.lurs.org.uk/UN293%20MAY%201986.pdf|journal=Underground News|volume=293|pages=59|issn=0306-8617|via=}}</ref>\n! colspan=\"6\" |Driving Motor Cars\nr\n! colspan=\"3\" |ntrol Trailerso\n! colspan=\"6\" |ailer Carsr\n|-\n! Year !![[Metropolitan Railway electric multiple units|Met Railway \u2116]] \n![[London Transport (brand)|London Transport \u2116]]\n!Year\n![[Metropolitan Railway electric multiple units|Met Railway \u2116]] \n![[London Transport (brand)|Londo